<br>
1. Lots of cool models for the Golden Deamon contests.  However, it ended real crapply as they showed us the winners (not the models, just the humans that painted them) and then announced the Slayer winner and we all went home.  Sort of a letdown.<br>
<br>
2. Tomb Kings looks awesome.  I got lots of pictures of the new release painted by the heavy metal team.  They will get posted soon.<br>
<br>
3. Codex: Deamonhunters looks realy cool.  Unfortantely the pictures I took came out realy crappy (thanks to the before mentioned ankle biters bugging the hell out of me!).  There will be troops in power armor, termie armour, and a new demonhunter dreadnought, though it looks realy close to the current loyalist dread.  The termies will be all plastic and have been totally redone and placed on a 40mm base.  Andy Chambers said he wanted to have termies look like they could actually fight in hand to hand combat.  All demonhunters will get +2 str weapons, some will also be power weapons and others will be force weapons.  This is so you can play and have a chance against non demons armies.  Demons will be -1 LD against DH.<br>
<br>
4. 40K Inquisiter models will be out soon.  They look realy nice as well. Got some good pics of them.<br>
<br>
5. This summer will be the 13th Crusade of Abbadon.  But you probably heard that already.  Plastic Cadians are a go, as is a choas cultist list, and other goodies associated with the big summer campaign.  Andy C. said this will be bigger than Armeggedon.  There will be some huge consequences after this war... I will believe it when I see it.<br>
<br>
6. Firewarrior, a first person shooter was released today.  You follow the life of a fire warrior in his passage by fire.  YOu can kill Space Marines.  THQ is using thier own engine to design the game.  I think that it will be ok, but nothing special in the FPS genre.  Except that you can kill Space Marines.  http://www.firewarrior.com to download the demo.  Password is gamesday.  The site goes live Monday morning.<br>
<br>
7. That is enough for me tonite.  I will post the pics tomorrow after I get some sleep. <p>Viva la Revelution!! <br>
